            <h1 class="font-weight-light">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p><strong>Last updated on December 26, 2019</strong></p>

            <h5>How does deploy2.org collect data about me?</h5>
            <p>deplo2y.org collects data about you:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>when you browse deplo2y.org</li>
                <li>when you use deplo2y.org deployment service</li>
                <li>when you contact deplo2y.org by e-mail for support or other help</li>
            </ul>
            <p>deplo2y.org does not buy or otherwise receive data about you from data brokers.</p>

            <h5>What data does deploy2.org collect about me, and why?</h5>

            <p>When you visit deploy2.org, whether you have an account or not, the site uses cookies, server logs, and other methods to collect data about what pages you visit and when.</p>

            <p>deploy2.org uses data about how you use the website to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>optimize the website, so it's quick and easy to use</li>
                <li>diagnose and debug technical errors</li>
                <li>defend the website from abuse and technical attacks</li>
                <li>compile statistics on icon popularity</li>
                <li>compile statistics on the kinds of software and computers visitors use</li>
            </ul>

            <h5>How can I make choices about data collection?</h5>
            <p>You're free to visit deploy2.org without using the service. You may also configure your web browser to disable cookies when visiting the website.</p>

            <p>You can opt out of Google Analytics using a <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">browser extension</a>.</p>

            <p>deploy2.org does not respond to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Do_Not_Track" target="_blank">Do Not Track HTTP header</a>.</p>

            <h5>Where does deploy2.org store data about me?</h5>
            <p>deploy2.org stores account data, data about website use, and data about content delivery network use on servers in the United States of America.</p>

            <p>Content delivery network servers are located worldwide, and store data about their use wherever they are located.</p>

            <h5>Does deploy2.org comply with the EU General Data Protection Regulation?</h5>
            <p>deploy2.org respects privacy rights under <a href="http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=uriserv:OJ.L_.2016.119.01.0001.01.ENG" target="_blank">Regulation (EU) 2016/679</a>, the European Union's General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Information that GDPR requires deploy2.org to give can be found throughout these questions and answers.</p>

            <h5>Does deploy2.org share data about me with others?</h5>
            <p>deploy2.org does not sell or give information about you to other companies or services. However, deploy2.org does use services from other companies to provide <i>deploy2.org</i>, content delivery networks, and to distribute and develop icons and software. The companies behind those services may collect data about you on their own, for their own purposes. Some of these services may be used to collect information about your online activities across different websites. All of these services are based in the United States.</p>

